Ketones and aldehydes are products of the partial oxidation of complex alcohols with mild oxidants (e.g. Pyridinium chlorochromate (PCC), Dess-Martin periodinane (DMP), Swern oxidation reagent). In particular, primary alchols produce aldehydes 
\begin{center}\chemfig{ -[:45]-[:-45]-[:45]OH }\ce{->[$[$ox$]$][]}\chemfig{  -[:45]-[:-45]()(-[:45]H)(=[:-90]O)}\end{center}
and secondary alcohols produce ketones:
\begin{center}\chemfig{ -[:45](-[:-45])(-[:90]OH)}\ce{->[$[$ox$]$][]}\chemfig{  -[:45]((-[:-45])(=[:90]O))}\end{center}